<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,474,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,387,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Material examined.</emphasis>
This species was common in most sites, in a way similar to its congener. We recorded one male from the Islas Marietas (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[663,720,510,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9298.0">9298</number>
A) and one ovigerous female (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[1235,1295,510,534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9298.0">9298</number>
C), with two females (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[426,485,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9303.0">9303</number>
B) and two ovigerous females (ICMyL MAZ 
<number box="[1023,1081,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="9303.0">9303</number>
C) from Estacahuite (
<geoCoordinate box="[1332,1431,546,570]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" precision="925" value="15.65">
<number box="[1332,1360,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="15.0">15</number>
° 
<number box="[1369,1400,546,570]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="39.0">39</number>
´N
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,258,582,606]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" precision="925" value="-96.46667">
<number box="[151,182,582,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="96.0">96</number>
° 
<number box="[191,221,582,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="28.0">28</number>
´W
</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,474,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,619,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Remarks.</emphasis>
The presence of this species in Mexican waters was confirmed by Wicksten &amp; Hernández (
<number box="[1340,1399,618,642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="2000.0">2000</number>
) in the southern Gulf of California. The northernmost sites were from the Loreto area by Hernández 
<emphasis box="[1240,1296,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1312,1374,654,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="2009.0">2009</number>
). Our study provides new sites along the Mexican coast as far south as Estacahuite, about 
<quantity box="[1117,1225,690,714]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" unit="km" value="1.9">1,900 km</quantity>
from the previous records.
</paragraph>
